==English==
[[File:Runic letter ansuz.png|thumb|100px|Runic letter {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr||ᚫ|tr=a|ansuz}}, source for Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letters replaced by ''A'']]

===Etymology 1===
From {{der-lite|en|enm|-}} and {{der-lite|en|ang|-}} upper case letter {{m-lite|enm|A}} and split of {{der-lite|en|enm|-}} and {{der-lite|en|ang|-}} upper case letter {{m-lite|enm|Æ}}.
* The {{der-lite|en|ang|-}} letters {{m-lite|ang|sc=Latnx|A}} and {{m-lite|ang|sc=Latnx|Æ}} replaced the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letters {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr|ᚪ||tr=a|āc}} and {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr|ᚫ||tr=æ|æsc}}, derived from the Runic letter {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr|ᚫ||tr=a|Ansuz}}, in the 7th century.

====Alternative forms====
