==Luxembourgish==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA-lite|lb|/aː/}}
** {{rhymes|lb|aː|s=1}}

===Etymology 1===

====Letter====
{{head-lite|lb|letters|lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|lb|letter|1|a}}

=====See also=====
* {{see-temp|list:Latin script letters/lb}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh-lite|lb|goh|ouga}}, from {{inh-lite|lb|gem-pro|sc=Latnx|*augô}}, ultimately from {{der-lite|lb|ine-pro|sc=Latnx|*h₃ekʷ-||eye; to see}}. The phonetic development in Luxembourgish is regular: Old High German ''-ou-'' becomes ''-ā-''; intervocalic ''-g-'' is lost; word-final short vowels are apocopated.

====Noun====
{{head-lite|lb|nouns|g=n|plural|Aen}}

# [[eye]]
#: {{ux-lite|lb|Ech hunn eppes am '''A.'''|I have something in my '''eye.'''}}

===Etymology 3===
From {{inh-lite|lb|gmh|ouwe}}, from {{inh-lite|lb|goh|ouwa}}, from {{inh-lite|lb|gem-pro|sc=Latnx|*awjō}}. Cognate with {{cog-lite|de|Aue}}, {{cog-lite|en|eyot}}, {{cog-lite|is|ey}}, {{cog-lite|da|ø}}, {{cog-lite|sv|ö}}.

====Noun====
{{head-lite|lb|nouns|g=f|plural|Aen}}

# {{lb|lb|only used in place names}} [[floodplain]], [[meadow]]

[[Category:lb:Anatomy]]

