==Norwegian Bokmål==
{{wikipedia|lang=nb}}

[[Image:Latin letter A.svg|250px|thumb|The [[letter]]  '''''A''''' from the [[Norwegian]] alphabet.]]

===Etymology===
From {{der-lite|nb|la|A}}, from {{der-lite|nb|grc|sc=Polyt|Α||tr=A|alpha}}, likely through the {{der-lite|nb|ett|-}} language, from {{der-lite|nb|phn|sc=Phnx|𐤀|tr=ʾ}}, from Proto-Canaanite [[Image:Protoalef.svg|20px]], from Proto-Sinaitic [[Image:Proto-semiticA-01.svg|20px]], from {{der-lite|nb|egy|sc=Egyp|𓃾}} representing the head of an [[ox]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA-lite|nb|/ɑː/}}
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA-lite|nb|/a/|/ɑː/}}
* {{audio|nb|Pronunciation of Norwegian Bokmål «A», «a».ogg|Audio}}
* {{rhymes|nb|ɑː}}
* {{hyphenation|nb|A}}
* {{homophones|nb|a|à|A-|a-|ah}}

===Letter===
{{head-lite|nb|letters|upper case||lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|nb|letter|1}}

====See also====
* {{list:Latin script letters/nb/simple}}

===Noun===
{{head-lite|nb|nouns|g=m|definite singular|A-en|indefinite plural|A-er|definite plural|A-ene}}

# the letter {{l-lite|nb|A}}
# {{lb|nb|horology}} symbol for {{l-lite|nb|avance}}
# {{lb|nb|physics}} symbol for {{l-lite|nb|ampere}}
# {{lb|nb|physics}} symbol for {{l-lite|nb|massetall||nucleon number}}

===Anagrams===
* {{anagrams|nb|a|A-|a-}}

