==Slovene==
{{wikipedia|lang=sl}}

===Etymology===
From Gay's Latin alphabet {{m-lite|sh|A}}, from {{der-lite|mul|cs|-}} alphabet {{m-lite|cs|A}}, from the {{der-lite|mul|ett|-}} letter {{m-lite|ett|sc=Ital|𐌀|tr=a}}, from the {{der-lite|mul|grc|-}} letter {{m-lite|grc|sc=Polyt|Α||tr=A|alpha}}, derived from the {{der-lite|mul|phn|-}} letter {{m-lite|phn|sc=Phnx|𐤀||tr=ʾ|[[aleph]]}}, from the {{der-lite|mul|egy|-}} hieroglyph {{m-lite|egy|sc=Egyp|𓃾}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{qualifier|phoneme|tonal variety}}: {{IPA|sl|/áː/|/àː/|/ʌ́/|/a/|[â]|[ǎ]}}
* {{qualifier|phoneme|non-tonal variety}}: {{sl-IPA|aː|a}}
* {{qualifier|letter name}}: {{sl-IPA|ā}}
* {{audio|sl|Sl-nt-á.ogg|Audio (letter name, non-tonal)}}
* {{rhymes|sl|aː}}
* {{homophones|sl|a}}

===Letter===
{{head-lite|sl|letters|upper case||lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|sl|letter|1}}
# {{Latn-def-lite|sl|langname=Resian|letter|1}}
# {{Latn-def-lite|sl|langname=Natisone Valley dialect|letter|1}}

===Noun===
{{sl-noun|Ā|m-in}}

# {{n-g-lite|The name of the [[Appendix:Latin script|Latin script]] letter '''''[[A]]''''' / '''''a'''''.}}

====Inflection====
* Overall more common
{{sl-decl-noun-m|Ā|Ā-j}}

* More common when with a definite adjective
{{sl-decl-noun-table2|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|Ā|title=Masculine inan., no endings}}

====Derived terms====
{{der4|sl|od A do Ž|ena A|od A do B|Á|Ä}}

===See also===
