==Tagalog==

===Etymology===
From {{bor-lite|tl|es|A}}. Each pronunciation has a different source:
* Filipino alphabet pronunciation is influenced by {{der-lite|tl|en|A}}.
* Abakada alphabet pronunciation is influenced by [[Baybayin]] character {{m-lite|tl|ᜀ|sc=Tglg|tr=a}}.
* Abecedario pronunciation is from {{der-lite|tl|es|A}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{hyph-lite|tl|A}} <!-- {{hyph|tl|A}} -->
* {{sense-lite|letter name|Filipino alphabet}} {{IPA-lite|tl|/ˈʔej/|[ˈʔɛɪ̯]}} <!-- {{tl-IPA}} -->
* {{sense-lite|letter name|Abakada alphabet|Abecedario}} {{IPA-lite|tl|/ˈʔa/|[ˈʔɐ]}} <!-- {{tl-IPA}} -->
* {{sense-lite|phoneme}} {{IPA-lite|tl|/a/|[ɐ]}} <!-- {{tl-IPA}} -->
* {{rhymes-lite|tl|a|ej|s=1}}

===Letter===
{{head-lite|tl|letters|upper case||lower case|a|Baybayin spelling|ᜁᜌ᜔|f3sc=Tglg|cat2=terms with Baybayin script}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|tl|letter|1|ey|alphabet name={{w|Filipino alphabet}}}}

===Letter===
{{head-lite|tl|letters|upper case||lower case|a|Baybayin spelling|ᜀ|f3sc=Tglg|cat2=terms with Baybayin script}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|tl|letter|1|a|alphabet name={{w|Abakada alphabet}}}}
# {{lb|tl|historical}} {{Latn-def-lite|tl|letter|1|a|alphabet name={{w|Filipino orthography#Adoption of the Latin script|Abecedario}}}}

