===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/bɹaʊn/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-brown.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|en|En-uk-brown.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
* {{rhymes|en|aʊn|s=1}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|countable|and|uncountable}} A [[colour]] like that of [[chocolate]] or [[coffee]].
#: {{ux|en|The '''browns''' and greens in this painting give it a nice woodsy feel.}}
#: {{color panel|623017}}
# {{lb|en|snooker|countable}} One of the [[colour]] balls used in [[snooker]], with a value of 4 points.
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} [[black tar|Black tar]] [[heroin]].
# {{lb|en|slang|archaic|countable}} A [[copper]] [[coin]].
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1853|author=Charles John Chetwynd Talbot|title=Meliora, Or, Better Times to Come|page=247
|passage=I know there are many persons — some who are themselves poor — who 'never turn a beggar from their door,' but always give them a few '''browns''' (halfpence) or some scran (broken victuals).}}
#* {{quote-book|en|title=London Town|year=1883|entry=The Omnibus
|url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:16_London_Town,_page_12.png
|text="We've not had any breakfast,—won't you toss us down a '''brown'''?"—<br/>That's what they call a penny in the streets of London Town.}}
# A brown horse or other animal.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1877|author=George Nevile|title=Horses and Riding|page=105|passage={{...}} '''browns''' are the soberest, bays are the worst tempered, and chestnuts are the most foolish.}}
# {{lb|en|sometimes capitalised|countable|informal}} A person of [[Latino]], [[Middle Eastern]] or [[South Asia]]n [[descent]]; a brown-skinned person; someone of [[mulatto]] or [[biracial]] appearance.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=2005|author=Kristen A. Myers|title=Racetalk: Racism Hiding in Plain Sight
|passage=Many '''browns''' and blacks are immigrants — some of whom have not yet become naturalized citizens of the United States.}}
# {{lb|en|entomology}} Any of various [[nymphalid]] butterflies of subfamily [[w:Satyrinae|Satyrinae]] (formerly the family {{taxlink|Satyridae|family|ver=180223}}).
# {{lb|en|entomology}} Any of certain species of [[nymphalid]] butterflies of subfamily [[w:Satyrinae|Satyrinae]], such as those of the genera ''{{w|Heteronympha}}'' and ''{{w|Melanitis}}''.
# {{lb|en|informal}} A {{l|en|brown trout}} (''[[Salmo trutta]]'').
# {{lb|en|hunting|as "the brown"}} A mass of [[bird]]s or [[animal]]s that may be indiscriminately fired at.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1928|author=R. Pigot|title=Twenty-five Years Big Game Hunting|page=166
|passage=The temptation to have a shot into the '''brown''' was great. There was not a head there which was not a big one and the one by himself was not too easy a shot since it is always difficult to shoot when lying in soft snow.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1979|author=Kevin Andrews|title=Athens Alive|page=223
|passage=My anger mounted at this, I opened the courtyard door and raised my musket to fire into the '''brown'''; I had loaded it with small shot, and if it had gone off that would have been the death of us and the ruin of all of us in the house.}}

