===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To become brown.
#: {{synonyms|en|q1=chiefly literary and poetic|embrown|brownify}}
#: {{ux|en|Fry the onions until they '''brown'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|title={{w|The Omnivore's Dilemma}}|author={{w|Michael Pollan}}|publisher=The Penguin Press|year=2006|ISBN=1594200823|passage=The chicken was '''browning''' nicely, the skin beginning to crisp and take on the toasty tones of oiled wood.|page=269}}
# {{lb|en|cooking|transitive}} To cook something until it becomes brown.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1887|title=Indian Cookery "Local" for Young Housekeepers: Second Edition|page=67
|passage=Pound an onion, warm a spoonful of ghee and throw in the onion, '''brown''' it slightly, add your curry stuff, '''brown''' this till it smells pleasantly, {{...}}}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|transitive}} To [[tan]].
#: {{ux|en|Light-skinned people tend to '''brown''' when exposed to the sun.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make brown or dusky.
#: {{synonyms|en|q1=chiefly literary and poetic|embrown}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1807|author=Joel Barlow|title={{w|The Columbiad}}|passage=A trembling twilight o'er the welkin moves, / '''Browns''' the dim void and darkens deep the groves.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To give a bright brown colour to, as to gun barrels, by forming a thin [[coating]] of [[oxide]] on their surface.
#* {{quote-book|en|1860|Andrew Ure|title=Ure’s Dictionary of Arts, Manufactures, and Mines|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Obl3pV1XWXUC&pg=PA463|page=463|passage=It is mixed uniformly with olive oil, and rubbed upon the iron slightly heated, which is afterwards exposed to the air, till the wished-for degree of '''browning''' is produced.}}
# {{lb|en|demography|transitive|intransitive|slang|ethnic slur|usually|derogatory|offensive}} To turn progressively more [[Hispanic]] or [[Latino]], in the context of the population of a geographic region.
#: {{ux|en|the '''browning''' of America}}

