==Middle English==

===Noun===
{{head|enm|noun}}

# {{alt form|enm|moneth}}

==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|Januarie}}, {{m|enm|januari}}, re-latinised forms of {{cog|enm|Janevere}}, {{m|enm|Ieneuer}}, from {{der|en|xno|genever}}, from {{bor|en|la|iānuārius||(month) of Janus}}, a compound of {{com|la|Iānus|-ārius||pos1="[[Janus]]"|pos2=adjectival suffix}}, with the first element perhaps from the [[Proto-Indo-European]] root {{m|ine-pro|*yeh₂-||to go}}. {{doublet|en|Gennaro}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/ˈd͡ʒæn.j(ʊ.)ə.ɹi/}} ''or as US''
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|jănʹyo͞o-ĕr'ē}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈd͡ʒænjuˌɛɹi/|/ˈd͡ʒænjuˌæɹi/}}
* {{a|AU}} {{IPA|en|/ˈd͡ʒænjʉˌeːɹi/|/ˈd͡ʒænjəɹi/|/ˈd͡ʒænɹi/}}
* {{a|obsolete}} {{IPA|en|/ˈd͡ʒɪnəˌwɛəɹi/|/ˈd͡ʒɪnəˌweɪɹi/}}<ref>{{R:Hall PGSMS|2|II.4|68}}</ref>
* {{audio|en|en-us-January.ogg|Audio (US)}}
